title: Celebrities other than Donald Trump who resemble fish
text: A longhorn cowfish caused quite the splash this week when its picture was put next to an image of Donald Trump - showing a striking resemblance. Everything about the aquatic animal was spot on, including the President's hair and his downturned expression. But the Donald is far from the first person to have been compared to an underwater creature. From Tulisa and Madonna to Victoria Beckham and Keira Knightly, below are our pick of celebrities who have been caught in rather fishy poses. In cod we trust: This longhorn cowfish bears a striking resemblence to U.S. President Donald Trump Posh seafood? Mrs Beckham cracks a rare smile (of sorts) and looks like she should be served with chips Golden gills: But only one of these toothy redheads is Belle de Jour actress Billie Piper Read my lips: Faye Dunaway and her pal could fighter sharks with these stern gurns Who's Donatella? A touch of tooth whitener and this scary coral reef trigger fish could be Ms Versace's doppelganger That's what you call a trout pout: X Factor judge Tulisa is a dead ringer for a lumpfish More channel than Chanel? A turret fish and Pirates Of The Caribbean star and model Keira Knightley Fishing for compliments: Madonna strikes a pose and ends up looking like this scorpionfish Down in the mouth: Britain's Got Talent's Amanda Holden has a sinking feeling this rockfish has a better tan than her Fancy a filler of fish? WAG Abbey Clancy's double is the appropriately named sweetlips Share or comment on this article 7
